WEBVTT

00:01.763 --> 00:03.504
-Previously on "Get Shorty"...

00:03.604 --> 00:04.786
-We need to get Amara
out of her house

00:04.886 --> 00:05.786
and away from her men.

00:05.887 --> 00:06.947
-I might have an idea.

00:07.048 --> 00:09.510
If you want to be together...

00:09.610 --> 00:10.791
-Ricky...

00:10.891 --> 00:12.473
-They're gonna shut down
the movie.

00:12.573 --> 00:13.554
-What?

00:13.654 --> 00:15.435
Is everything about you a lie?

00:15.535 --> 00:17.397
Hold on.
-What are you do--

00:17.497 --> 00:19.599
-Even your eyebrows are a lie.

00:19.699 --> 00:21.601
-I'm leaving Greg.

00:21.701 --> 00:23.963
I haven't told him yet,
but I've decided.

00:24.063 --> 00:25.484
-We're stopping
through Palm Springs

00:25.585 --> 00:26.686
without bringing extra security?

00:26.786 --> 00:28.567
-It's where we get married.

00:28.667 --> 00:30.569
-Some of the things you do
to other people...

00:30.669 --> 00:32.411
they bother me.

00:32.511 --> 00:34.533
-Why do you say that now?

00:34.633 --> 00:36.535
-The Feds promised
we won't do time.

00:36.635 --> 00:39.177
-Yeah, didn't they also promise
that they would wait six months

00:39.277 --> 00:41.299
before they moved in?

00:41.399 --> 00:42.660
-Trust me, okay?

00:42.760 --> 00:44.762
-Hands, hands.
On your feet.

00:45.883 --> 00:47.785
-When did you last see her
in this room?

00:47.885 --> 00:49.887
-A -- A minute ago!

00:59.376 --> 01:01.718
-Why do you say that now?

01:01.818 --> 01:06.482
[ Cellphone chimes ]
-Because...

01:06.582 --> 01:10.125
if I don't say it now, then --
then I never will.

01:10.225 --> 01:12.728
♪♪♪

01:12.828 --> 01:15.010
[ Cellphone chimes ]

01:15.110 --> 01:16.531
♪♪♪

01:16.631 --> 01:19.494
-Wait outside.

01:19.594 --> 01:24.058
♪♪♪

01:24.158 --> 01:28.903
[ Bryan Adams' "Heaven" plays ]

01:29.003 --> 01:32.466
♪♪♪

01:32.566 --> 01:36.550
-♪ Oh, thinkin' about
all our younger years ♪

01:36.650 --> 01:38.151
[ Cellphone chimes ]

01:38.251 --> 01:41.514
♪ There was only you and me ♪
[ Cellphone chimes ]

01:41.614 --> 01:45.798
♪ We were young and wild
and free ♪

01:45.898 --> 01:48.200
♪ Now nothin' can take you
away from me ♪

01:48.300 --> 01:49.441
[ Door slams open ]

01:49.542 --> 01:52.084
-Freeze, freeze!
-Search warrant! On the ground.

01:52.184 --> 01:55.007
[ Lock engages ]
Hands. Show me hands!

01:55.107 --> 01:56.688
-♪ But that's over now ♪

01:56.788 --> 01:58.330
-FBI! Open the door.

01:58.430 --> 02:01.012
-Hey! Ah, damn it, cops.
What did I do?

02:01.112 --> 02:02.734
Hey, get your fucking hands
off me!

02:02.834 --> 02:05.016
-♪ Baby,
you're all that I want ♪

02:05.116 --> 02:08.659
♪ When you're lyin' here
in my arms ♪

02:08.759 --> 02:12.022
♪ I'm findin' it hard
to believe ♪

02:12.122 --> 02:15.746
♪ We're in heaven ♪

02:15.846 --> 02:19.029
♪ And love is all that I need ♪

02:19.129 --> 02:22.512
♪ And I found it there
in your heart ♪

02:22.612 --> 02:25.635
♪ It isn't too hard to see ♪

02:25.735 --> 02:27.797
♪ We're in heaven ♪

02:27.897 --> 02:29.438
[ Door closes ]

02:29.538 --> 02:32.080
[ Police radio chatter ]

02:32.181 --> 02:32.841
♪♪♪

02:32.941 --> 02:35.644
[ Glass shattering ]

02:35.744 --> 02:39.007
-Ohh!

02:39.107 --> 02:40.648
-Outside,
anybody have eyes on her?

02:40.748 --> 02:42.730
The alley behind the hotel?

02:42.830 --> 02:45.453
-[ Groaning ]

02:45.553 --> 02:46.654
[ Sirens wail in distance ]

02:46.754 --> 02:48.255
[ Groans ]

02:48.355 --> 02:51.618
-♪ Bring you up
when you're feeling down ♪

02:51.718 --> 02:53.180
-[ Grunts ]

02:53.280 --> 02:55.702
-♪ Yeah, nothin' could change
what you mean to me ♪

02:55.802 --> 02:57.784
[ Sirens wailing in distance,
helicopter blades whirring ]

02:57.884 --> 03:01.187
♪ Oh, there's lots
that I could say ♪

03:01.287 --> 03:02.588
-Oh! Oh.

03:02.689 --> 03:04.710
-♪ But just hold me now ♪

03:04.810 --> 03:08.634
♪ 'Cause our love
will light the way ♪

03:08.734 --> 03:11.877
♪ And, baby,
you're all that I want ♪

03:11.977 --> 03:14.920
♪ When you're lyin' here
in my arms ♪

03:15.020 --> 03:17.122
-[ Coughs ]
[ Vehicle approaching ]

03:17.222 --> 03:18.723
Hey!

03:18.823 --> 03:20.285
Hey, help!

03:20.385 --> 03:23.367
-♪ ...a knife to my breast ♪

03:23.468 --> 03:25.329
-What happened?

03:25.429 --> 03:26.490
-Thank you.

03:26.590 --> 03:28.452
-Do you need me to call someone?

03:28.552 --> 03:30.014
Ohh!

03:30.114 --> 03:32.776
-♪ If you keep from the demons
who knock at your door ♪

03:32.876 --> 03:34.137
♪♪♪

03:34.237 --> 03:38.021
♪ Won't you come back
to see me again? ♪

03:38.121 --> 03:41.544
♪ Won't you come back someday? ♪
[ Body thuds ]

03:41.644 --> 03:45.428
♪ Oh, I've tried and I've tried
to make my way from here ♪

03:45.528 --> 03:48.150
♪ But I'm stuck
at heaven's gate ♪

03:48.250 --> 03:51.293
[ Engine revs, tires screech ]

03:53.615 --> 03:56.878
[ Siren chirping,
indistinct conversations ]

03:56.978 --> 03:58.680
-Heard they're calling
an ambulance.

03:58.780 --> 04:00.001
-Driver had
a pickup truck stolen.

04:00.101 --> 04:01.282
We think it was Amara.

04:01.382 --> 04:03.604
-And she hurt the guy?
-Critically.

04:03.704 --> 04:05.246
-Holy shit.
[ Sighs ]

04:05.346 --> 04:07.728
And --
And you couldn't find her?

04:07.828 --> 04:08.929
How'd she get past
all these guys?

04:09.029 --> 04:10.210
-What was she wearing?

04:10.310 --> 04:13.774
-Wearing, uh...a wedding dress.

04:13.874 --> 04:15.976
That should stand out, right?

04:16.076 --> 04:18.578
Her hair's all done up, and --

04:18.678 --> 04:20.099
Oh.

04:20.200 --> 04:22.462
Oh, my God,
the fucking engagement ring.

04:22.562 --> 04:24.463
-The one you bought or...
-Oh, the line of credit

04:24.564 --> 04:26.345
that I opened up for that...

04:26.445 --> 04:27.746
-Okay.

04:27.847 --> 04:30.949
You were in the bedroom,
you told her she looked nice.

04:31.050 --> 04:33.992
Then you went into the suite?

04:34.092 --> 04:36.995
-There was some back-and-forth.
I mean...

04:37.095 --> 04:39.677
I said I appreciated her.

04:39.777 --> 04:43.321
I don't always like the way
she treats other people.

04:43.421 --> 04:44.802
-You said that?

04:44.902 --> 04:46.283
-Yeah, no big deal.

04:46.384 --> 04:48.926
I was just --
I was laying it all out there.

04:49.026 --> 04:51.208
-Why?
-I told her.

04:51.308 --> 04:55.792
I said, "If I don't tell you
this now, then I never will."

04:57.634 --> 05:00.136
I meant before we get married.

05:00.236 --> 05:02.138
Not before the Feds move in.

05:02.238 --> 05:04.300
Don't -- Don't --
Stop that look.

05:04.400 --> 05:06.342
It wasn't me
that tipped her off, okay?

05:06.442 --> 05:09.385
-Looking back, will she think
that you knew about the raid?

05:09.485 --> 05:11.487
-What?! No.

05:13.528 --> 05:16.111
Will she?

05:16.211 --> 05:19.594
-Well, "Wylderness,"
it's such an amazing project.

05:19.694 --> 05:22.717
I mean, I just --
I just can't let it go.

05:22.817 --> 05:25.079
Yeah.

05:25.179 --> 05:27.561
So, we on for March, or what?

05:27.661 --> 05:30.124
They got a course
that's right on the ocean.

05:30.224 --> 05:32.686
I'm still licking my wounds
from Augusta.

05:32.786 --> 05:35.088
[ Chuckles ]

05:35.188 --> 05:38.291
All right, so, one more thing.

05:38.391 --> 05:41.814
Have you got any updates
on Miles Daly?

05:41.914 --> 05:44.697
Miles Daly. He's one
of the guys who was indicted.

05:44.797 --> 05:46.979
And Phil was telling me
that they're only thinking

05:47.079 --> 05:50.102
of pressing minor charges?

05:50.202 --> 05:54.266
Well, so -- so, is he getting
off on a technicality, or...

05:54.366 --> 05:55.987
No, I know, I know.
There's -- There's --

05:56.087 --> 05:59.430
There's some things
that you can't tell me.

05:59.531 --> 06:02.754
But here's the thing.
[ Sighs ]

06:02.854 --> 06:04.875
Miles was running the operation.

06:04.976 --> 06:08.919
And he was violent towards me,
personally.

06:09.019 --> 06:10.601
Now, I can't go on the record,

06:10.701 --> 06:16.126
but I think it would be
a mistake to -- to...

06:16.226 --> 06:17.807
Yeah.

06:17.907 --> 06:20.690
Yeah, you get what I'm saying.

06:20.790 --> 06:22.612
Yeah.

06:22.712 --> 06:27.016
-There were several federal
indictments that were issued.

06:27.116 --> 06:29.818
-So, everyone I worked with

06:29.918 --> 06:33.141
was involved in
a massive criminal conspiracy.

06:33.241 --> 06:36.705
Only, I had no idea,
because I'm sheltered and naive.

06:36.805 --> 06:39.787
Sorry about the mess.

06:39.888 --> 06:41.389
I've been taking some time off.

06:41.489 --> 06:42.950
-Right.

06:43.050 --> 06:45.833
Uh, you notice anything odd

06:45.933 --> 06:48.515
during production
of "The Admiral's Mistress"?

06:48.616 --> 06:52.399
-Everyone was uptight
around Amara,

06:52.499 --> 06:55.642
but that's not unusual
with an investor.

06:55.742 --> 06:59.966
In Nevada,
some of the crew had guns.

07:00.066 --> 07:03.930
-Who had guns?

07:04.030 --> 07:06.972
-All of them...

07:07.072 --> 07:08.974
I think?

07:09.074 --> 07:13.158
And, uh,
one of our sets burned down.

07:16.441 --> 07:19.864
Are you writing
"She's an idiot"?

07:19.964 --> 07:22.627
You should be.

07:22.727 --> 07:25.950
-Who arranged the transfer
of funds into the LLC?

07:26.050 --> 07:27.031
-I don't know.

07:27.131 --> 07:29.233
I didn't have nothing
to do with that.

07:29.333 --> 07:33.276
-Mr. De Escalones,
not only is your signature

07:33.377 --> 07:34.958
on the articles
of incorporation --

07:35.058 --> 07:38.161
The LLC is literally named
after you.

07:38.261 --> 07:40.123
-'Cause I was set up.

07:40.223 --> 07:41.924
They didn't tell me
what I was signing.

07:42.024 --> 07:44.287
-Mr. De Escalones
was manipulated

07:44.387 --> 07:47.009
by a sophisticated
criminal organization.

07:47.109 --> 07:49.111
-I was manipulated.

07:51.473 --> 07:53.375
-So, uh...

07:53.475 --> 07:56.418
these transcripts are, uh --

07:56.518 --> 07:58.900
are from recordings
made by an operative

07:59.000 --> 08:02.503
and a Title III wiretap
at Budd E. Boy Entertainment.

08:02.603 --> 08:06.187
Direct quotes
of things that you've said.

08:06.287 --> 08:09.870
February 22nd --
"I'm supposed to oversee this.

08:09.970 --> 08:14.314
The movie.
I mean, like, the money."

08:14.414 --> 08:18.037
February 25th --
"The finances and shit?

08:18.138 --> 08:21.521
That all runs through me."

08:21.621 --> 08:23.923
February 26th --

08:24.023 --> 08:26.005
"I'm Yago, God damn it!

08:26.105 --> 08:28.607
I'm the king of this bitch."

08:28.707 --> 08:31.230
February 28th...

08:34.112 --> 08:37.215
-Will you excuse me?

08:37.315 --> 08:39.777
[ Breathes deeply ]

08:39.878 --> 08:42.019
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

08:42.120 --> 08:44.342
You holding up?

08:44.442 --> 08:46.704
-Looking forward to going home.
Who was that?

08:46.804 --> 08:48.946
-My boss.
[ Clears throat ]

08:49.046 --> 08:51.048
Have a seat.

08:54.131 --> 08:56.393
[ Door closes ]

08:56.493 --> 08:58.495
[ Sighs ]

09:02.178 --> 09:05.441
Someone very high up
wants to make an example of you.

09:05.541 --> 09:08.364
-That guy that just walked out?

09:08.464 --> 09:11.326
-Someone in
the Department of Justice.

09:11.426 --> 09:12.688
They're saying our deal with you

09:12.788 --> 09:15.130
was contingent
on Amara's arrest,

09:15.230 --> 09:16.891
and since that didn't happen --

09:16.992 --> 09:18.373
-Hold on, hold on.

09:18.473 --> 09:21.015
Just so we don't, um...

09:21.115 --> 09:23.377
[ Scoffs ]

09:23.477 --> 09:25.860
You're standing by the deal
that we made, right?

09:25.960 --> 09:29.203
-No. No.

09:31.525 --> 09:34.427
I have tried calling in
every favor I have.

09:34.528 --> 09:35.869
I've been on the phone
for hours.

09:35.969 --> 09:37.670
-I should have known.
I should have fucking...

09:37.771 --> 09:39.772
[ Chuckles ]

09:40.893 --> 09:42.034
Louis told me.

09:42.135 --> 09:44.136
Oh, he'll love this.

09:46.298 --> 09:48.801
Meanwhile, I'm -- I'm --
I'm promising my daughter --

09:48.901 --> 09:50.402
I'm saying, "Don't you worry,
sweetheart..."

09:50.502 --> 09:52.084
-Miles.
-"...'cause this lovely

09:52.184 --> 09:53.965
lady cop,
she -- she gave me her word.

09:54.065 --> 09:55.527
And -- And look!

09:55.627 --> 09:58.129
She's number-one grandma,
so she won't fuck me over.

09:58.229 --> 09:59.971
Long as I turn rat
and drag my buddy into it."

10:00.071 --> 10:02.733
-I will fight to help you on
any part of this I can control.

10:02.834 --> 10:04.775
I will insist
the terms of the plea deal

10:04.875 --> 10:06.497
be at least as short as --
-Oh, really?

10:06.597 --> 10:08.178
'Cause you want
another deal now.

10:08.279 --> 10:10.260
You want another deal.
One where I go away.

10:10.360 --> 10:13.623
-For as short a stretch
as possible.

10:13.724 --> 10:15.986
-How long is that?

10:16.086 --> 10:17.787
-The case against you is strong.

10:17.887 --> 10:20.310
But if the only charge
is laundering,

10:20.410 --> 10:21.951
that's only five years.

10:22.051 --> 10:23.512
You will be out in two.
-No!

10:23.613 --> 10:24.754
-Two years!
-No!

10:24.854 --> 10:26.876
-You'll be out!

10:26.976 --> 10:28.077
-No.

10:28.177 --> 10:30.078
No!

10:30.179 --> 10:32.000
No!
[ Clatter ]

10:32.100 --> 10:34.523
No!

10:34.623 --> 10:35.724
-Ah!

10:35.824 --> 10:36.765
We're fine.

10:36.865 --> 10:38.086
-Are we fine?!

10:38.186 --> 10:40.008
Is that what we are?!

10:40.108 --> 10:41.769
-Please.

10:41.869 --> 10:43.010
-[ Scoffs ]

10:43.110 --> 10:45.112
-We're fine.

10:46.033 --> 10:48.495
[ Door closes ]

10:48.595 --> 10:50.297
[ Lock engages ]

10:50.397 --> 10:52.099
I don't blame you, not --

10:52.199 --> 10:54.201
-Fuck you!

11:01.687 --> 11:03.769
Ohh.

11:10.055 --> 11:13.318
-Oh, bunny, I'm sorry.

11:13.418 --> 11:16.641
[ Jazz music plays ]

11:16.741 --> 11:25.569
♪♪♪

11:25.669 --> 11:34.257
♪♪♪

11:34.357 --> 11:36.740
-From the description
of your conversation with Amara,

11:36.840 --> 11:39.062
it's possible she has no idea
you're working with us.

11:39.162 --> 11:41.264
-Yes, and it's also possible
she does.

11:41.364 --> 11:43.185
-Hard to assess
the degree of threat.

11:43.286 --> 11:46.188
There's some indication
that she's left the country.

11:46.288 --> 11:48.110
Even if she did,
it wouldn't stop her

11:48.210 --> 11:49.231
from ordering another hit.

11:49.331 --> 11:50.993
-Another hit?

11:51.093 --> 11:53.155
-Lila Llambias, a cartel member.

11:53.255 --> 11:54.436
We assume it was Amara.

11:54.536 --> 11:57.158
Shot in the back.
Actually survived.

11:57.258 --> 11:59.681
-Oh, geez.

11:59.781 --> 12:01.282
-It's up to you.

12:01.382 --> 12:04.125
Resume your life,
put it out of your mind.

12:04.225 --> 12:05.966
Or there's witness protection.

12:06.066 --> 12:10.090
-Oh, and spend the rest
of my life in Oklahoma,

12:10.190 --> 12:12.132
working
at a fucking Jamba Juice?

12:12.232 --> 12:14.094
-I like Jamba Juice.

12:14.194 --> 12:16.136
-[ Sighs ]

12:16.236 --> 12:18.238
Is there a door number three?

12:20.239 --> 12:22.461
-Prison.
-Right.

12:22.562 --> 12:23.743
-Serve a long enough sentence,

12:23.843 --> 12:25.504
no one will know
you were an informant.

12:25.604 --> 12:28.107
-Yeah, and I get shanked
on the first day.

12:28.207 --> 12:29.228
-It's...

12:29.328 --> 12:31.550
You'd be
at a minimum-security facility.

12:31.650 --> 12:34.032
King Bush Federal
is mostly non-violent offenders,

12:34.132 --> 12:37.275
so the beatings and the sexual
assaults you're worried about --

12:37.375 --> 12:38.796
non-existent.

12:38.897 --> 12:42.620
There's recreational activities.
There's free counseling.

12:44.782 --> 12:47.204
-Y-You're
actually pitching this?

12:47.304 --> 12:49.126
That I <i>choose</i> to go to prison?

12:49.226 --> 12:52.669
-You asked
about door number three.

12:56.993 --> 12:59.255
-[ Sighs ]

12:59.355 --> 13:01.257
♪♪♪

13:01.357 --> 13:03.179
You got pictures of this place?

13:03.279 --> 13:05.821
[ Jazz music plays ]

13:05.921 --> 13:07.142
[ Door opens ]

13:07.243 --> 13:08.824
-Thank you.

13:08.924 --> 13:15.590
♪♪♪

13:15.690 --> 13:17.692
Coffee.

13:20.575 --> 13:22.356
Sorry to rush you, but...

13:22.456 --> 13:24.478
need to know
what you're thinking.

13:24.578 --> 13:26.320
-Vanilla-flavored creamer.

13:26.420 --> 13:29.002
Who likes this stuff?

13:29.103 --> 13:30.644
-What did your lawyer say?

13:30.744 --> 13:32.766
-[ Sighs ]

13:32.866 --> 13:35.448
That I'm fucked.

13:35.548 --> 13:37.971
-Fight this,
you won't like the result.

13:38.071 --> 13:41.614
-Is five years
the best you can do?

13:41.714 --> 13:43.716
-Yes.

13:46.759 --> 13:49.421
-Can I go home
for a couple of days before?

13:49.521 --> 13:51.763
-If you wear an ankle monitor.

13:58.850 --> 14:02.793
-Wherever I do the time, it
needs to be somewhere nearby...

14:02.893 --> 14:04.915
so that my kid
can come and visit.

14:05.015 --> 14:08.519
-The closest Federal facility
is maximum-security.

14:08.619 --> 14:10.961
There is a medium-security.
It's four hours away.

14:11.061 --> 14:12.282
-Has to be close.

14:12.382 --> 14:13.924
-It's up to you.

14:14.024 --> 14:16.686
I'll get your lawyer.
We'll go over the terms.

14:16.786 --> 14:19.168
-You said someone high up
has it in for me.

14:19.269 --> 14:21.851
Just me?

14:21.951 --> 14:24.854
I'm asking, can you honor
Louis' side of the deal?

14:24.954 --> 14:27.136
-I don't know.

14:27.236 --> 14:30.219
-He has a baby on the way.

14:30.319 --> 14:33.902
Be nice if the kid
got to know its dad.

14:34.002 --> 14:35.664
He didn't know anything
about this

14:35.764 --> 14:37.826
until I dragged him into it.

14:37.926 --> 14:42.210
So if you're gonna honor just
one of the promises you made...

14:43.731 --> 14:46.273
-I'll try.
[ Knocking ]

14:46.373 --> 14:48.455
[ Buzzer, door opens ]

14:50.337 --> 14:52.339
[ Door closes ]

15:08.754 --> 15:10.756
-Thanks.

15:16.441 --> 15:19.784
-So, the Book of Mormon says
no drinking, no pre-marital sex.

15:19.884 --> 15:22.266
But you get a pass
on white-collar crime?

15:22.366 --> 15:23.948
-The reason that they let me off

15:24.048 --> 15:26.350
is because I was
on the periphery of this thing.

15:26.450 --> 15:28.712
-You knew
Amara was laundering money.

15:28.812 --> 15:30.714
-I just...

15:30.814 --> 15:33.436
really wanted my screenplay
to get made.

15:33.537 --> 15:36.359
It's not a good excuse.

15:36.459 --> 15:38.401
-The <i>L.A. Times,</i> um...

15:38.501 --> 15:41.284
they had an article about Amara.

15:41.384 --> 15:43.165
They think
that she had people killed.

15:43.265 --> 15:46.288
-Yeah, I-I read that...

15:46.388 --> 15:49.531
and, uh, I mean, I figured
she was just a casino owner

15:49.631 --> 15:52.494
who was, you know,
skirting around the law

15:52.594 --> 15:55.377
here and there, but...

15:55.477 --> 15:59.220
I mean,
do I seem like a killer?

15:59.320 --> 16:00.661
-[ Chuckles ]

16:00.762 --> 16:02.863
-[ Chuckling ] Right?
So...

16:02.964 --> 16:06.467
-I know, but there are things
that you <i>did</i> know.

16:06.567 --> 16:08.148
And you didn't tell me.

16:08.248 --> 16:12.152
-Well, look, on the one hand, I
want to be honest with my wife.

16:12.252 --> 16:13.353
That's a tenet of my faith.

16:13.453 --> 16:15.795
But on the other hand,
there are times

16:15.895 --> 16:18.438
that being honest
isn't doing you any favors.

16:18.538 --> 16:20.359
-But you're being honest now?

16:20.460 --> 16:22.862
-I mean, now I am.

16:24.743 --> 16:30.409
-Oh, you lied to me
for a really long time.

16:30.509 --> 16:32.050
It's hard to get past that.

16:32.150 --> 16:33.892
-So, tell me.

16:33.992 --> 16:36.114
What can I do to make it right?

16:38.396 --> 16:40.518
-I don't know that you can.

16:41.439 --> 16:44.201
No, I'm -- I'm gonna need time.

16:47.925 --> 16:49.927
-Okay.

16:54.331 --> 16:56.513
-Do you have a place to stay?

16:56.613 --> 16:59.195
-Yeah, yeah.

16:59.295 --> 17:00.716
I'm...

17:00.817 --> 17:02.758
staying at the Ramada
by the airport.

17:02.858 --> 17:05.361
It's -- It's pretty nice.

17:05.461 --> 17:09.244
-[ Breathes deeply ]

17:09.344 --> 17:11.987
-I'm gonna get my things.

17:24.598 --> 17:26.880
[ Footsteps approaching ]

17:30.484 --> 17:33.466
-Sorry.
We have people over.

17:33.567 --> 17:35.428
-I didn't realize.

17:35.528 --> 17:36.669
-No, it's okay.

17:36.769 --> 17:38.511
They're just Greg's friends.

17:38.611 --> 17:42.435
Just took me a minute
to get away.

17:42.535 --> 17:46.118
So...this is it?

17:46.218 --> 17:47.760
<i>-Is</i> it?

17:47.860 --> 17:50.362
I was thinking in five years'
time, we could just...

17:50.462 --> 17:52.364
pick up right where we left off.

17:52.464 --> 17:54.466
-Perfect.

17:56.307 --> 17:57.929
It was on the news.

17:58.029 --> 18:00.491
Not you, but, um, the case.

18:00.591 --> 18:02.593
-Yeah, I know.

18:04.635 --> 18:06.937
-Did you [Sighs]

18:07.037 --> 18:11.421
I mean, did you know
what you were getting into?

18:11.521 --> 18:14.104
You did.

18:14.204 --> 18:16.546
-It's complicated.
-[ Breathes deeply ]

18:16.646 --> 18:20.189
Seems like there's a lot
of interesting things about you

18:20.289 --> 18:22.952
that I don't know.

18:23.052 --> 18:25.074
-That's a nice way
of putting it.

18:25.174 --> 18:27.176
[ Both chuckle ]

18:29.538 --> 18:31.560
-You been to prison before?

18:31.660 --> 18:34.482
-I got in some trouble
in Ireland, as a kid.

18:34.582 --> 18:35.563
Nothing like this.

18:35.663 --> 18:38.366
But...I'll be okay.

18:38.466 --> 18:40.468
-Okay.

18:44.431 --> 18:47.054
-Did you, um...

18:47.154 --> 18:49.296
Did you talk to your husband
in the end?

18:49.396 --> 18:51.818
-No, we're not splitting up.

18:51.918 --> 18:56.302
I was, uh -- I was
going through something, and...

18:56.402 --> 18:58.805
it's better now.

19:00.566 --> 19:01.507
-Good to hear.

19:01.607 --> 19:03.849
-[ Laughs ] Yeah?

19:09.094 --> 19:11.476
Well.

19:11.576 --> 19:13.578
You take care.

19:14.699 --> 19:17.962
-You too.

19:18.062 --> 19:20.525
[ Chuckles ]

19:20.625 --> 19:22.787
-Um...

19:31.755 --> 19:34.557
[ Footsteps departing ]

19:37.760 --> 19:40.943
[ Indistinct conversations,
mid-tempo music plays ]

19:41.043 --> 19:46.548
♪♪♪

19:46.648 --> 19:48.150
-Hey, hon?

19:48.250 --> 19:50.312
-I'll be right in.

19:50.412 --> 19:58.039
♪♪♪

19:58.139 --> 20:05.866
♪♪♪

20:18.638 --> 20:19.739
[ Engine shuts off ]

20:19.839 --> 20:22.581
-Here you go.

20:22.682 --> 20:24.623
-Mmm.

20:24.723 --> 20:26.105
[ Gasps ]
Look at that.

20:26.205 --> 20:28.627
-Yeah,
I figured, "Why not?"

20:28.727 --> 20:32.070
-With the hot paprika and all.
-[ Chuckles ]

20:32.170 --> 20:35.673
-Trying to fatten me up
before I go away.

20:35.774 --> 20:38.256
-Bet food's not this good
in prison.

20:40.017 --> 20:43.240
-In fact, I believe they buy
their meat from carnivals.

20:43.340 --> 20:45.963
-Tell Dad
what you did in school.

20:46.063 --> 20:48.966
-Mr. Kovach showed us
how to melt pennies

20:49.066 --> 20:50.607
over a Bunsen burner.

20:50.707 --> 20:52.169
Pour the zinc into a bowl.

20:52.269 --> 20:54.210
We all got to try it.
[ Chuckles ]

20:54.310 --> 20:57.734
-Well, glad to hear they're
putting the money I sent them

20:57.834 --> 20:59.735
to good use.
[ Ringtone plays ]

20:59.836 --> 21:02.658
-No phones.
-It's for bio homework.

21:02.758 --> 21:04.180
I promised I'd call Marquita.

21:04.280 --> 21:07.102
-All right.
-We'll wait for you.

21:07.202 --> 21:09.965
-Hey.
Just give me one second.

21:13.528 --> 21:15.530
[ Door closes ]

21:18.092 --> 21:22.116
-If it were me, I'd indulge
myself in one "I told you so."

21:22.216 --> 21:24.878
-Yeah, I don't think
I could make you feel worse

21:24.979 --> 21:26.980
than you do already.

21:30.183 --> 21:36.249
-For what it's worth,
which I know is fuck all,

21:36.349 --> 21:38.671
I am sorry.

21:42.795 --> 21:44.917
-So am I.

21:51.923 --> 21:53.265
[ Emma laughing ]
-Yeah, strong-willed.

21:53.365 --> 21:55.507
[ Laughing ] I suppose.
-Dad!

21:55.607 --> 21:57.629
-Well, you'd been going on
about it for like six months.

21:57.729 --> 21:59.630
-Okay, but that's not my fault!

21:59.730 --> 22:02.393
Their ads were on constantly.
I was brainwashed.

22:02.493 --> 22:06.877
-Oh, okay. So, I give in, and
we pay for this Frostey Freeze.

22:06.977 --> 22:08.158
Strawberry.
-[ Laughing ] Ohh.

22:08.258 --> 22:09.960
-And within 30 seconds...
-No.

22:10.060 --> 22:12.242
-Within 30 seconds,
the whole thing was gone.

22:12.342 --> 22:14.324
Now, I presumed
that you spilled it.

22:14.424 --> 22:16.326
-And then I puked.
-Projectile.

22:16.426 --> 22:18.768
-[ Laughing ] Eww!
-[ Laughing ] So I...

22:18.868 --> 22:22.691
So I-I gave the manager
20 bucks. I cleaned up a bit.

22:22.792 --> 22:25.654
And we got back to the car,
and you told me...

22:25.754 --> 22:27.696
9 years old...

22:27.796 --> 22:29.498
and you sa--

22:29.598 --> 22:31.500
-What?

22:31.600 --> 22:33.682
I told you what?

22:35.323 --> 22:37.465
-[ Sobs ]

22:37.565 --> 22:40.147
-Dad.

22:40.248 --> 22:43.651
-[ Voice breaking ]
I thought it was gonna work out.

22:45.853 --> 22:47.855
-Oh, Dad.

22:49.456 --> 22:52.519
I-I can see you.

22:52.619 --> 22:55.201
We can visit.

22:55.301 --> 22:57.644
-[ Sniffles ]

22:57.744 --> 23:02.508
-Everything sucks right now,
but it won't suck forever.

23:06.271 --> 23:08.093
-I should get that
tattooed somewhere.

23:08.193 --> 23:11.496
-Dad, you just need to find
a way to get through it.

23:11.596 --> 23:13.598
It'll be all right.

23:14.799 --> 23:17.081
Just come home.

23:20.244 --> 23:22.386
Dad...

23:22.486 --> 23:24.268
Okay.

23:24.368 --> 23:26.730
-[ Crying ]

23:27.891 --> 23:30.414
-[ Crying ]

23:34.337 --> 23:36.339
[ Keys jangling ]

23:37.860 --> 23:40.022
[ Keys clatter ]

24:01.882 --> 24:05.285
[ Wind gusting ]

24:07.968 --> 24:14.914
♪♪♪

24:15.014 --> 24:16.796
[ Birds chirping ]

24:16.896 --> 24:25.644
♪♪♪

24:25.744 --> 24:34.492
♪♪♪

24:34.592 --> 24:43.340
♪♪♪

24:43.440 --> 24:51.908
♪♪♪

24:52.008 --> 25:00.956
♪♪♪

25:01.057 --> 25:09.945
♪♪♪

25:16.951 --> 25:19.854
[ Jazz music plays ]

25:19.954 --> 25:21.956
-Wow.

25:23.757 --> 25:25.259
Why'd you have to crack it open?

25:25.359 --> 25:27.501
-Searching
for a hidden compartment.

25:27.601 --> 25:29.603
Standard procedure.

25:31.244 --> 25:33.747
-Yeah, well, it was a gift.

25:33.847 --> 25:36.269
Well, I was in it twice.

25:36.369 --> 25:44.937
♪♪♪

25:46.058 --> 25:49.081
-Feeling sentimental?

25:49.181 --> 25:50.802
That wasn't a joke.

25:50.902 --> 25:53.965
-You know...

25:54.065 --> 25:57.628
Amara had some great qualities.

25:58.910 --> 26:00.911
[ Sighs ]

26:03.194 --> 26:05.636
End of an era.

26:06.517 --> 26:09.619
♪♪♪

26:09.720 --> 26:12.422
-Hey.

26:12.522 --> 26:14.524
-Hey.

26:19.208 --> 26:21.210
-Make yourself at home.

26:23.092 --> 26:26.195
I figured there was
no point renting a place

26:26.295 --> 26:28.837
for half a decade.

26:28.937 --> 26:30.919
Since I'll have free lodgings,

26:31.019 --> 26:33.601
courtesy of the U.S. taxpayer.

26:33.701 --> 26:34.883
-Mm.

26:34.983 --> 26:37.605
You're welcome.

26:37.705 --> 26:39.207
-[ Chuckles ]

26:39.307 --> 26:41.649
Ginger ale?
-Yeah, yeah.

26:41.749 --> 26:44.732
-You ever get tired
of drinking ginger ale?

26:44.832 --> 26:46.493
-Oh, I've...

26:46.593 --> 26:48.295
come to hate it.

26:48.395 --> 26:49.936
But, you know,
people get uncomfortable

26:50.036 --> 26:51.778
if you don't have a drink.

26:51.878 --> 26:53.880
[ Can slides ]

26:56.082 --> 26:58.024
So, just lay it on me.

26:58.124 --> 27:00.906
What happened with your deal?
-[ Sighs ]

27:01.007 --> 27:02.708
Someone weighed in
from the Department of Justice.

27:02.808 --> 27:04.109
-Yeah,
that's what my lawyer said.

27:04.209 --> 27:05.911
They're -- They're
in Washington, D.C.

27:06.011 --> 27:07.312
Why are they bothering you?

27:07.412 --> 27:09.514
-I've been thinking on that.

27:09.614 --> 27:10.956
-And?

27:11.056 --> 27:14.159
-Did you know that Laurence Budd
got the movie going again?

27:14.259 --> 27:18.162
After the Feds shut it down.
-[ Sighs ]

27:18.262 --> 27:22.166
-Now, who has the power
to rein in the FBI?

27:22.266 --> 27:25.889
The Department of Justice.

27:25.989 --> 27:32.175
-S-- So you're saying that
Laurence Budd got you sent away?

27:32.275 --> 27:34.457
-He and I had a bit of a run-in.

27:34.557 --> 27:37.620
-Yeah?
How bad of a run-in?

27:37.720 --> 27:39.141
-Bad enough, apparently.

27:39.242 --> 27:42.344
-That he'd have you put away?
-I'd blame him.

27:42.444 --> 27:44.026
-Okay, well,
what are we gonna do?

27:44.126 --> 27:45.627
-[ Sighs ]
-I'll go over there.

27:45.727 --> 27:47.269
I'll take care of it myself.
-No, no.

27:47.369 --> 27:49.711
-Well, we're not
gonna let it go.

27:49.811 --> 27:53.034
-I have no intention
of letting it go.

27:53.134 --> 27:55.797
I'm saying,
for now, we stay clear of him.

27:55.897 --> 27:57.078
I mean, he went this far

27:57.178 --> 28:00.041
just 'cause I tore off
one of his eyebrows.

28:00.141 --> 28:01.922
Oh, the man has fake eyebrows.

28:02.022 --> 28:03.123
-What the f--

28:03.224 --> 28:04.925
[ Laughs ]
Fucking...

28:05.025 --> 28:05.966
[ Can opens ]

28:06.066 --> 28:07.447
...Hollywood, man.

28:07.547 --> 28:09.770
I mean...

28:09.870 --> 28:11.331
-Wait. What?

28:11.431 --> 28:15.014
-I'm just saying,
if you don't like your eyebrows,

28:15.114 --> 28:18.457
just deal with it, you know?

28:18.558 --> 28:19.899
-[ Chuckles ]
-What?

28:19.999 --> 28:21.380
-Well...
-I mean...

28:21.480 --> 28:23.462
-No, it's a medical condition.

28:23.562 --> 28:25.744
Did you think
it was, like, a fad?

28:25.844 --> 28:26.985
-Well...
-[ Laughs ]

28:27.085 --> 28:29.187
You think that, like,
men in Hollywood are going out,

28:29.287 --> 28:30.869
getting fake eyebrows, that...

28:30.969 --> 28:33.031
-There's crazier shit out there.
-No, there's not.

28:33.131 --> 28:35.513
-Ye--
-That's an insane thought, Lu.

28:35.613 --> 28:38.156
[ Laughing ]
You think that...

28:38.256 --> 28:39.997
Hollywood men are getting...

28:40.097 --> 28:42.459
[ Both laugh ]

28:45.102 --> 28:47.864
-[ Clears throat ]
-I'm so fucked.

28:51.908 --> 28:54.931
And I feel bad
'cause I-I pulled you in.

28:55.031 --> 28:56.292
-Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no.

28:56.392 --> 28:58.174
I mean, the only reason
that I'm not doing time

28:58.274 --> 29:01.177
is because of you.

29:01.277 --> 29:03.859
All that shit I gave you, and...

29:03.959 --> 29:06.942
[Sighs]
now you're the one going away.

29:07.042 --> 29:09.044
It's...

29:11.286 --> 29:13.288
-Well, you got a kid on the way.

29:17.131 --> 29:19.133
-Wyatt.

29:21.655 --> 29:22.876
-Wyatt?

29:22.977 --> 29:24.678
-Yeah.

29:24.778 --> 29:26.360
Yeah.

29:26.460 --> 29:29.042
-I hope you do better by
your kid than I've done by mine.

29:29.142 --> 29:30.524
-[ Scoffs ]
Listen, you've fucked up

29:30.624 --> 29:32.125
a lot of things in your life.

29:32.225 --> 29:34.207
Emma's not one of them.

29:34.307 --> 29:36.309
She's amazing.

29:40.152 --> 29:42.735
Hey.

29:42.835 --> 29:45.617
We're gonna look after
each other.

29:45.717 --> 29:47.719
Okay?

29:51.162 --> 29:52.984
-Wyatt.

29:53.084 --> 29:55.566
[ Chuckles ]

29:59.450 --> 30:01.512
[ Buzzer ]
-Gates open.

30:01.612 --> 30:03.774
[ Indistinct shouting ]

30:13.303 --> 30:15.084
-Come on, man!

30:15.184 --> 30:17.346
[ Shouting continues ]

30:21.350 --> 30:23.092
-Gates closing.

30:23.192 --> 30:25.354
[ Shouting continues ]

30:28.517 --> 30:31.079
[ Indistinct shouting, jeering ]

30:39.206 --> 30:41.368
[ Shouting, jeering continues ]

30:46.813 --> 30:49.936
-How we doing?!
-What up, big man?!

30:51.217 --> 30:55.081
-One at a time,
on the footsteps.

30:55.181 --> 30:57.083
Let's go.
-Move along.

30:57.183 --> 30:58.324
-Towels off.

30:58.424 --> 31:00.086
Shake 'em out.

31:00.186 --> 31:01.967
Drop 'em.

31:02.067 --> 31:04.069
Tongues.

31:06.992 --> 31:08.133
Gums.

31:08.233 --> 31:10.235
All around.

31:12.437 --> 31:14.439
Turn around.

31:15.600 --> 31:17.301
Bottom of your right foot.

31:17.401 --> 31:19.263
[ Door closes ]
-Clear.

31:19.363 --> 31:22.186
-Bottom of your left foot.

31:22.286 --> 31:24.488
-Clear.
-Bend over.

31:25.529 --> 31:27.311
Spread your cheeks.
Cough.

31:27.411 --> 31:29.412
[ Men coughing ]

31:31.414 --> 31:34.157
[ Classical music plays ]

31:34.257 --> 31:42.244
♪♪♪

31:42.344 --> 31:50.171
♪♪♪

31:50.272 --> 31:58.059
♪♪♪

31:58.159 --> 31:59.260
-Thanks.

31:59.360 --> 32:03.444
♪♪♪

32:12.972 --> 32:16.035
[ Doorbell rings ]

32:16.135 --> 32:17.637
-Can I help you?

32:17.737 --> 32:20.359
-Uh, yeah.
Uh...

32:20.459 --> 32:22.701
I'm here to go to prison?

32:25.464 --> 32:27.125
[ Lock engages ]
-Hey!

32:27.225 --> 32:29.227
[ Keys jangling ]

32:37.275 --> 32:39.096
[ Door closes ]

32:39.196 --> 32:40.898
-[ Clears throat ]

32:40.998 --> 32:43.000
[ Cellphone closes ]

32:44.441 --> 32:46.443
[ Footsteps approaching ]

32:47.404 --> 32:49.406
[ Radio beeps ]

32:56.012 --> 33:00.035
[ Buzzer, door opens ]

33:00.136 --> 33:01.877
[ Classical music plays ]

33:01.977 --> 33:04.880
[ Keys jangling ]

33:04.980 --> 33:09.084
♪♪♪

33:09.184 --> 33:10.325
[ Knocking ]

33:10.425 --> 33:20.334
♪♪♪

33:20.434 --> 33:23.337
[ Toilet flushes ]

33:23.437 --> 33:26.420
♪♪♪

33:26.520 --> 33:28.301
-Oh, hey.
-Hey.

33:28.401 --> 33:29.903
-You must be Rick.

33:30.003 --> 33:32.425
Clifford Bernhardt.
Everyone calls me Clive.

33:32.525 --> 33:34.427
-Oh, okay.
-"Lights out" is in 10,

33:34.527 --> 33:36.669
so I'll let you get settled.

33:36.769 --> 33:39.392
If you're hungry, I've got
cookies my daughter made.

33:39.492 --> 33:41.473
They're pretty good.
She uses peppermint oil.

33:41.574 --> 33:43.876
-Yeah, thanks. Not feeling
that hungry right now.

33:43.976 --> 33:44.997
-Well, no worries.

33:45.097 --> 33:47.399
Change your mind,
they're in the fridge.

33:47.499 --> 33:52.163
♪♪♪

33:52.263 --> 33:56.327
Earplugs on your pillow
in case you're a light sleeper.

33:56.427 --> 34:00.331
I've been known to snore.

34:00.431 --> 34:01.932
-Thanks.

34:02.032 --> 34:04.615
[ Jazz music plays ]

34:04.715 --> 34:07.657
-Amazing what time off can do.

34:07.758 --> 34:09.940
-Actually, I've been busy
prepping my case

34:10.040 --> 34:12.502
against the company.

34:12.602 --> 34:14.304
-Except you don't have a case.

34:14.404 --> 34:16.345
-My attorney disagrees.

34:16.446 --> 34:17.987
-Which is their job.

34:18.087 --> 34:21.110
-I just gave the HR department
a detailed summary

34:21.210 --> 34:25.314
of my version of the events
leading up to my suspension.

34:25.414 --> 34:28.597
I don't think
it'll match with Emily's.

34:28.697 --> 34:32.000
-Speaking of
your uncorroborated story...

34:32.100 --> 34:34.402
the whole
"two-way mirror" thing --

34:34.502 --> 34:37.565
You realize that sounds insane.

34:37.665 --> 34:41.128
-I also had a chance
to research drywall.

34:41.228 --> 34:44.892
Turns out every board has
a stamp of when it was made.

34:44.992 --> 34:46.573
So the drywall in that closet

34:46.673 --> 34:49.256
won't match the drywall
used to seal the mirror.

34:49.356 --> 34:51.398
-Fascinating.

34:54.681 --> 34:56.062
What do you want?

34:56.162 --> 34:57.423
Money?

34:57.523 --> 34:59.265
-No.
-I'd offer you back your job,

34:59.365 --> 35:01.787
but your history of working
with convicted felons --

35:01.887 --> 35:04.910
-I would rather drink bleach
than be your executive.

35:05.010 --> 35:07.312
-Ah. So?

35:07.412 --> 35:09.754
-I'm staying on "Wylderness"
as a producer,

35:09.854 --> 35:11.356
like it says in my contract.

35:11.456 --> 35:14.519
-You don't think that could be
awkward, us working together?

35:14.619 --> 35:16.621
-Not if you stay out of my way.

35:21.625 --> 35:23.367
-Anything else?

35:23.467 --> 35:25.489
-[ Sighs ]

35:25.589 --> 35:27.731
